Cell[BoxData["\<\"When we plug \[CapitalBeta](r) into the remaining \
equations, they are each a page long and I can't find an algebraic \
combination that simplifies them. However, the terms on the LHS of \
\\!\\(\\*SubscriptBox[\\(R\\), \\(11\\)]\\)-\\!\\(\\*SubscriptBox[\\(R\\), \
\\(44\\)]\\) all have the same denominator, and the RHS is zero. So, we can \
ignore the denominators:\"\>"], "Print",
