Cell[BoxData["\<\"The numerator divided by r \\!\\(\\*SuperscriptBox[\\(\
\[CapitalBeta]\\), \\(2\\)]\\) is strictly a function of t, ever so slightly \
different than Case b. In order for the whole expression to be strictly a \
function of t, the denominator divided by r \\!\\(\\*SuperscriptBox[\\(\
\[CapitalBeta]\\), \\(2\\)]\\) must equal some function of t, say \
\[ScriptF](t).\"\>"], "Print",
